.TH GRAFANA-UTIL-DASHBOARD-INSPECT-EXPORT 1 "2026-04-03" "grafana-util 0.8.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
grafana\-util\-dashboard\-inspect\-export \- Analyze dashboard export directories with operator\-summary and report\-contract views.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B grafana-util dashboard inspect-export [\fIOPTIONS\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
Analyze dashboard export directories with operator\-summary and report\-contract views.
.PP
Use this when you want to read a local export tree, inspect its structure, or render governance and dependency reports without contacting Grafana.
.SH COMMON OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-\-import\-dir
dashboard export root to inspect.
.TP
.B \-\-input\-format
choose raw or provisioning.
.TP
.B \-\-input\-type
select raw or source when the export root has multiple dashboard variants.
.TP
.B \-\-report
render table, csv, json, tree, tree\-table, dependency, dependency\-json, governance, or governance\-json views.
.TP
.B \-\-output\-format
single\-flag output selector.
.TP
.B \-\-interactive
open the shared inspect workbench.
.TP
.B \-\-output\-file
write the result to disk.
.TP
.B \-\-no\-header
suppress table\-like headers.
.SH EXAMPLES
.PP
Analyze dashboard export directories with operator\-summary and report\-contract views.
.EX
grafana-util dashboard inspect-export --import-dir ./dashboards/raw --input-format raw --table
.EE
.SH SEE ALSO
\fBgrafana-util\fR(1),
\fBgrafana-util-dashboard\fR(1)
